11 and the safety and welfare of specific individuals or the general public.
12 (f) (1) This subsection does not apply to a conviction of a crime for which
13 registration on the sex offender registry is required under Title 11, Subtitle 7 of this article.
14 (2) If a period of 7 years or more has passed since an applicant completed
15 serving the sentence for a crime, including all imprisonment, mandatory supervision,
16 probation, and parole, and the applicant has not been charged with another crime other
17 than a minor traffic violation, as defined in § 10–101 of this article, during that time, [a]
18 THE department may not deny an occupational license or certificate to the applicant solely
19 on the basis that the applicant was previously convicted of the crime.
